criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age ≥ 18 - ≤ 65 years;

          2. Male or non-pregnant female;

          3. Informed virtual pre-consent and paper signed consent forms;

          4. Absence of COVID-19 symptoms at time of screening;

          5. Symptomatic household with confirmed COVID-19 infection;

          6. Sharing the same premise/flat with a COVID-19 patient at least 8 hours per day;

          7. Unprotected (without mask) close contact lasting more than 4 hours with a coughing
             person who has been further confirmed COVID-19

          8. The duration of contact with the first patient with COVID-19 is less than 14 days

          9. Subject understands and agrees to comply with study procedures including triple blood
             analysis for anti-SARS-CoV-2 IgG in the case of the disease;

         10. Subject has a smartphone and can make photocopies of documents using a smartphone and
             send them via messengers.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. COVID-like symptoms in the previous 6 months ;

          2. Vaccination against SARS-CoV-2 in the previous 12 months;

          3. Risk for the complicated course of COVID-19 due to:

             3.1. Hypertension; 3.2. Diabetes mellitus; 3.3. Immunosuppressive conditions; 3.4.
             Chronic pathology of the respiratory system ; 3.5. Chronic pathology of the
             cardiovascular system ; 3.6. Malignant tumor ; 3.7. Systemic inflammatory connective
             tissue disease ; 3.8. Cerebrovascular disease ; 3.9. Chronic hepatitis. Hepatic
             cirrhosis; 3.10. Inflammatory bowel diseases ; 3.11. Chronic kidney disease ;

          4. Drug or alcohol abuse as suspected by investigator;

          5. History of persistent diarrhea of any cause;

          6. Use of pre- or probiotics during the last 2 weeks before inclusion or current use;

          7. Allergy to any components of the TDS;

          8. Technical difficulties to perform virtual study visits.

          9. Inability to perform a blood test for antibodies after 6 months

         10. Inability to swallow capsules, or choking / coughing while eating
